<%- contentFor('headContent') %>
<title><%= title %></title>

<%- contentFor('body') %>
<main class="container page-content">
  <div class="content-wrapper">
    <h1 class="page-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">How is the weather data collected?</h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            The current weather app uses the API from Open Weather Map:
            <a
              href="https://openweathermap.org/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >openweathermap.org</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">How accurate is the weather forecast?</h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Weather forecasts are typically accurate for 3-5 days in advance.
            The further into the future, the less accurate the prediction
            becomes due to the chaotic nature of atmospheric conditions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">How often is the weather data updated?</h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Current weather data is updated every 10 minutes to ensure you have
            the most recent information available.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">
          Can I get weather information for any location?
        </h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            Yes! Our service allows you to search for weather information for
            most cities worldwide. Simply enter the city name and country code
            in the search box.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">
          What does the "feels like" temperature mean?
        </h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>
            The "feels like" temperature takes into account factors like
            humidity and wind speed to give you a better idea of how the weather
            will actually feel to you, rather than just the thermometer reading.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</main>

<%- contentFor('scripts') %> <% if (typeof scripts !== 'undefined') { %>
<script src="<%= scripts %>"></script>
<% } %>
